SIMPLE: guiltless
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Guiltless
<hw>Guilt"less</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Free from guilt;
innocent.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The Lord will not hold him <qex>guiltless</qex> that taketh his
name in vain.</q> <rj><qau>Ex. xx. 7.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Without experience or trial; unacquainted
(with).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Such gardening tools, as art, yet rude,⟦br⟧
<qex>Guiltless</qex> of fire, had formed.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Guilt"less*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Guilt"less*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>guilt-ridden</ent>⟦br⟧
